  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Validate Binary Search Tree\n\nReturn whether a binary tree satisfies strict BST ordering: every left descendant is smaller and every right descendant is larger.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: root = [5,1,7,null,null,6,9]\nOutput: true\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: root = [5,1,7,null,null,4,9]\nOutput: false\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: root = [2,2,3]\nOutput: false\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- The judge provides a `TreeNode` class with `val`, `left`, and `right` fields.\n- Trees are shown in level-order form with `null` for missing children.\n- Node counts are sized for local offline execution.",
  "editorial": "Carry an exclusive lower and upper bound for every subtree. A node must fit inside all ancestor-imposed bounds.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def isValidBST(self, root):\n        def valid(node, low, high):\n            if not node:\n                return True\n            if node.val <= low or node.val >= high:\n                return False\n            return valid(node.left, low, node.val) and valid(node.right, node.val, high)\n        return valid(root, float('-inf'), float('inf'))\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Checking only parent-child relationships is not enough.",
    "Bounds become tighter as recursion descends."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def isValidBST(self, root):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
    "class_name": "Solution",
    "method_name": "isValidBST"
  },
  "checker": {
    "type": "exact"
  },
  "time_limit_ms": 2000,
  "memory_limit_mb": 256,
